<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2122] Remove controller.message.queue.size Config</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2122</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A deadlock can happen during a delete topic if controller.message.queue.size is overridden to a custom value. Details are here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2046?focusedCommentId=14380776&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-14380776&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2046?focusedCommentId=14380776&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-14380776&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Given that &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1993&quot; title=&quot;Enable topic deletion as default&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-1993&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-1993&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is enabling delete topic by default, it would be unsafe to simultaneously allow a configurable controller.message.queue.size&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
